@drpngx I face the same issue. I just pulled everything from master and tried to build the inference interface but I ran into the same error. I use bazel 0.14.
When I try to build it for arm64-v8a I get :

@protobuf_archive//:js_embed' failed (Exit 1)
/usr/local/google/buildbot/src/android/gcc/toolchain/build/../gcc/gcc-4.9/libgcc/unwind-dw2-fde-dip.c:461: error: undefined reference to 'dl_iterate_phdr'

But when I try to build for armeabi-v7a I get:

error executing command 
  (cd /home/saeid/.cache/bazel/_bazel_saeid/4c831e5c90ed5552b6fa9660252640e9/execroot/org_tensorflow && \
  exec env - \
    PATH=/home/saeid/Android/Sdk/platform-tools:/home/saeid/android-ndk-r14b:/home/saeid/bin:/home/saeid/.local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/db/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/jre/bin \
  /bin/bash -c 'source external/bazel_tools/tools/genrule/genrule-setup.sh; bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/bin/external/protobuf_archive/js_embed external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/any.js external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/struct.js external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/timestamp.js > bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/genfiles/external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types_embed.cc')
/bin/bash: bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/bin/external/protobuf_archive/js_embed: cannot execute binary file: Exec format error
Target //tensorflow/contrib/android:libtensorflow_inference.so failed to build

@drpngx  I face the same issue. I just pulled everything from master and tried to build the inference interface but I ran into the same error. I use bazel 0.14.
When I try to build it for arm64-v8a I get : 
```
@protobuf_archive//:js_embed' failed (Exit 1)
/usr/local/google/buildbot/src/android/gcc/toolchain/build/../gcc/gcc-4.9/libgcc/unwind-dw2-fde-dip.c:461: error: undefined reference to 'dl_iterate_phdr'
```

But when I try to build for armeabi-v7a I get:
```
error executing command 
  (cd /home/saeid/.cache/bazel/_bazel_saeid/4c831e5c90ed5552b6fa9660252640e9/execroot/org_tensorflow && \
  exec env - \
    PATH=/home/saeid/Android/Sdk/platform-tools:/home/saeid/android-ndk-r14b:/home/saeid/bin:/home/saeid/.local/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/local/bin:/usr/sbin:/usr/bin:/sbin:/bin:/usr/games:/usr/local/games:/snap/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/db/bin:/usr/lib/jvm/java-8-oracle/jre/bin \
  /bin/bash -c 'source external/bazel_tools/tools/genrule/genrule-setup.sh; bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/bin/external/protobuf_archive/js_embed external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/any.js external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/struct.js external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types/timestamp.js > bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/genfiles/external/protobuf_archive/src/google/protobuf/compiler/js/well_known_types_embed.cc')
/bin/bash: bazel-out/armeabi-v7a-opt/bin/external/protobuf_archive/js_embed: cannot execute binary file: Exec format error
Target //tensorflow/contrib/android:libtensorflow_inference.so failed to build
```
